    "extras": [
      "October to March is the easiest all-round weather window for Muscat, inland forts, Sharqiya Sands and Jebel Akhdar; summer heat is punishing in the north and center.",
      "Sultan Qaboos Grand Mosque is free, but arrive early, dress conservatively and avoid Friday tourist planning because visiting hours are limited around prayers.",
      "A basic 2WD rental works for Muscat, Sur, Nizwa and Salalah city/coast driving, but Jebel Akhdar officially requires a 4WD past the checkpoint and many desert camps prefer one too.",
      "Mwasalat is reliable on core city-to-city corridors like Muscat–Nizwa and Muscat–Sur, but it will not fully replace a car for wadis, camps, forts and mountain villages.",
      "Desert camps often include dinner and breakfast in the room rate, so the biggest extra spend in Wahiba is usually transfers, dune bashing, camel rides and sunrise excursions.",
      "Salalah is geographically disconnected from the classic Muscat–Nizwa–Sur loop, so an Oman Air domestic leg is the simplest way to include Dhofar without burning two or three long transit days."
    ],
